---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import app1 from '../../assets/app1.webp';
import app2 from '../../assets/app2.webp';
import app3 from '../../assets/app3.webp';
import app4 from '../../assets/app4.webp';
---

<div class='other-container'>
  <div class='others-wrapper'>
    <p class='other-overtext'>React / Typescript</p>
    <div class='other one'>
      <Image
        loading={'eager'}
        class='other-img'
        src={app1}
        alt='landing page'
      />
    </div>
    <h3 class='other-text'>
      My first application written based on experience from the financial
      industry and drawing on knowledge from client work.
    </h3>
    <h3 class='other-text'>
      Helps to quickly calculate returns on both bank deposits and investment
      funds, without the need for online calculators. Try my app <a
        aria-label='link to app site'
        href='https://letscountit.netlify.app/'>- Let's Count It.</a
      >
    </h3>
  </div>

  <div class='others-wrapper'>
    <p class='other-overtext'>Canva / Figma</p>
    <div class='other two'>
      <Image
        loading={'eager'}
        class='other-img'
        src={app2}
        alt='set of e-book covers'
      />
    </div>
    <h3 class='other-text'>
      Design and production of an interior design e-book for one of majors
      interior influencer in Poland.
    </h3>
    <h3 class='other-text'>
      A big challenge with this project was learning new tools such as Canva and
      Figma. The aforementioned e-books were a great addition to the website I
      created. <a
        aria-label='link to app site'
        href='https://stowidokowhome.pl/'
      >
        - stowidokow.home</a
      >
    </h3>
  </div>

  <div class='others-wrapper'>
    <p class='other-overtext'>Canva / Figma / Photoshop</p>
    <div class='other three'>
      <Image
        loading={'eager'}
        class='other-img'
        src={app3}
        alt='set of e-book covers'
      />
    </div>
    <h3 class='other-text'>
      Cooperation on the development of the website resulted in the creation of
      6 ebooks for the only housing lottery of its kind in Poland<a
        aria-label='link to spelnij-marzenia site'
        href='https://www.spelnij-marzenia.pl/'
      >
        - Spe≈Çnij Marzenia.</a
      >
    </h3>
    <h3 class='other-text'>
      Creating the graphics for the e-books allowed me to strengthen my skills
      as a graphic designer and contributed to a project in which winning the
      top prize helped to change the lives of people.
    </h3>
  </div>

  <div class='others-wrapper'>
    <p class='other-overtext'>SCSS / JavaScript</p>
    <div class='other four'>
      <Image
        loading={'eager'}
        class='other-img'
        src={app4}
        alt='landing page'
      />
    </div>
    <h3 class='other-text'>
      Simple dashboard showing examples of social media statistics<a
        aria-label='social dashboard'
        href='https://jerrywski.github.io/social-dashborad-switch-dark-light/'
      >
        - Social Dashoboard.</a
      >
    </h3>
    <h3 class='other-text'>
      One of the first challenges from Frontend Mentor, where I used a solution
      to change the light and dark colour of the background and elements on the
      page.
    </h3>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .other-container {
    margin-top: 50px;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    display: grid;
    gap: 50px;
    z-index: 10;
    position: relative;
  }
  .others-wrapper {
    border: none;
    border-radius: 15px;
    display: grid;
    padding: 5px;
    grid-template-rows: subgrid;
    grid-row: span 4;
    gap: 0px;
  }
  .other {
    border-radius: 15px;
  }
  .other.one {
    background-color: rgb(191, 205, 235);
  }
  .other.two {
    background-color: rgb(236, 117, 48);
  }
  .other.three {
    background-color: var(--bg-black);
  }
  .other.four {
    background-color: rgb(61, 115, 196);
  }
  .other-img {
    object-fit: contain;
    max-width: 100%;
    padding: 15px 0;
    display: block;
    height: 100%;
  }
  .other-overtext {
    margin-bottom: 5px;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-family: var(--second-font);
    color: var(--light-grey);
  }
  .other-text {
    margin-top: 10px;
    font-family: var(--second-font);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: inherit;
  }
  .other-text a {
    color: var(--bg-black);
  }
</style>
